Sheâ€™s a Park Explorer at Ichetucknee Springs State Park- DBJ
Grades: K, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5

Springs and their runs are described as one of the most productive freshwater systems on planet Earth.  At Ichetucknee Springs State Park, many springs combine together to make one gigantic spring run, the Ichetucknee River!  This river is one of the most pristine in Florida.  Not only is it great fun to canoe, snorkel, and tube, but the Ichetucknee River is also home to an amazing variety of plants and animals.  Park rangers work hard to keep the river clean and protected.  To make sure it stays healthy, they use many tools to determine its condition, such as monitoring chemicals in the water, measuring its flow, and keeping watch on its wildlife.  We are going to be learning about some of these techniques, and hands-on activities will include a demonstration of how the aquifer works, fun games, water-sampling, and protecting aquatic animals. Fun patch provided. Park entrance fee included.

*This event is for 2016 registered Girl Scouts, and registered & approved adult volunteers.
* For safety and supervision reasons, troops and individuals are not permitted to bring non-Girl Scouts or siblings. 
*Girl/adult ratios must be followed and adults are expected to stay on the premises during the event. 

$8/girl, $8/adult
